Description: Sherd of pottery dish or flat bowl with wide flat rim and flat foot, minimally offset from wall; two spool-shaped attachments on outside of rim in lieu of handle; traces of red paint on one spool. A smear of paint on the exterior lower wall (as on 1965,0930.187 and 189) is akin to marks indicating joins, though it appears ancient.
Curator's comments: Close to 1965,0930.187 and 189 but with slightly different profile.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.690)
